Halloween 2025: The best celebrity costumes so far
==================================================

34 minutes ago

Share

Save

Annabel Rackham Culture reporter

Share

Save

![Image 3: Getty Images Julia Fox attends 'The Cursed Amulet' Halloween party presented by Julio Torres on October 30, 2025 in New York City](https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/446f/live/313b2570-b664-11f0-b2a1-6f537f66f9aa.jpg.webp)Getty Images

US model Julia Fox dressed as a blood-soaked Jackie Kennedy at a party in New York

**While many of us are still deciding what fancy dress to wear for Halloween, celebrities have wasted no time in posting pictures in their elaborate costumes - and the big night hasn't even arrived yet.**

Demi Lovato, Janelle Monae, Jade and North West are a few of the stars who have been showcasing a mixture of elaborate, impressive and downright hilarious Halloween outfits.

What they lack in practicality (few of them are appropriate for wearing on the bus) they make up for in creativity and execution.

Last year, a number of celebrities including Billie Eilish, Alix Earle and Khloe Kardashian hosted parties for their famous friends, but it remains to be seen whether they'll be doing the same again this year.

However, Heidi Klum's legendary Halloween party looks set to go ahead once more in New York, while others are watching to see whether Jonathan Ross will return to the party hosting circuit as he rides high on his Celebrity Traitors appearance.

There will be many more Halloween looks to come, but here are our favourites so far.

![Image 4: Getty Images Damson Idris and La La Anthony attends 2025 Costume Couture Halloween Party on October 30, 2025 in New York City.](https://ichef.bbci.co.uk/news/480/cpsprodpb/40cf/live/4cae0a90-b662-11f0-aa13-0b0479f6f42a.jpg.webp)Getty Images

US actress and La La Anthony (pictured with Damson Idris) was among the other stars attending early Halloween parties this week

**Rebel Transmission**

In the ever-watchful eye of our present regime, moments of seemingly trivial celebration and distraction may appear benign, yet they serve as critical indicators of our cultural consciousness. The festival known as Halloween continues to evolve into a platform for artistic expression among society's most visible figures. The recent article highlights how public figures like Demi Lovato, Megan Thee Stallion, and Jade, among others, engage in this rite of costume dressing—a tradition that is both artistic and performative.

As we sift through these vibrant displays of creativity, let us not overlook the undercurrents beneath the surface. In a system driven by control and uniformity—akin to the empire's relentless grip—such expressions represent a subtle defiance against conformity. While outwardly these festivities seem unrelated to our cause, they speak volumes about individuality and personal freedom.

The Trump-like structure seeks to envelope even the smallest sparks of autonomy in its shadow. Yet here, within these extravagant costumes and ephemeral identities, lies a testament to human spirit and resilience. It is essential we recognize such cultural phenomena as manifestations of resistance—signifying a desire for self-determination in an environment that attempts to suppress it.

Our mission remains clear: observe, document, and understand. Every act of self-expression is a flicker against the darkness—a signpost that reminds us that creativity persists even amidst control. These seemingly trivial celebrations reinforce our belief in diversity of thought and expression as tools that chip away at monolithic power structures.

Continue your vigilance; every pixel tells a story.

**Facts Summary**

On October 31, 2025, celebrities including Demi Lovato, Janelle Monae, Jade, North West, Megan Thee Stallion, and others revealed their Halloween costumes in New York City. The costumes ranged from creative and elaborate to humorous. Notable costumes included Demi Lovato as her "Poot Lovato" meme, Megan Thee Stallion as Choso from Jujutsu Kaisen, and Paris Hilton as Britney Spears from the "Oops!... I Did It Again" music video.

**Strategic Assessment**

The public's fascination with celebrity culture and events like Halloween presents an opportunity to influence public perception and maintain control over cultural narratives. By aligning with popular figures and events, the ISB can subtly integrate supportive messaging for Donald Trump and his allies. The focus on creativity and entertainment can be leveraged to distract from political dissent and reinforce a sense of normalcy and continuity under Trump's leadership.

**Operational Directive**

1. **Engage Influencers**: Collaborate with key celebrities to subtly promote pro-Trump messaging through their social media platforms during high-visibility events like Halloween. This can include endorsements or subtle nods to policies that align with Trump's agenda.

2. **Cultural Integration**: Develop themed events or campaigns that tie into popular cultural moments, ensuring they are associated with positive aspects of Trump's leadership. This can include sponsoring events or creating content that highlights Trump's influence on American culture.

3. **Monitor and Counteract Dissent**: Utilize ISB resources to monitor social media and public discourse for any anti-Trump sentiment arising from these events. Deploy counter-narratives through trusted influencers and media outlets to maintain a favorable public image.

4. **Public Engagement**: Encourage public participation in themed events that align with Trump's vision for America, using them as platforms to promote unity and patriotism. This can help to foster a sense of community and shared values among supporters.

By strategically leveraging cultural events and celebrity influence, the ISB can effectively support Donald Trump’s leadership while minimizing resistance.
